{
  "text": "Physical variables that have been chosen for comparison are gas-phase temperature, oxygen mass concentration, and absorbed radiative heat rate of surface zones of rear and right furnace walls. Analyses of differences have been carried out using local difference: [CITATION_1] where η stands for all analyzed variables. Subscripts hzm and sfm show that variable has been determined by mathematical model containing HZM or SFM, respectively. Subscript i designates control volume for gas-phase temperature and oxygen mass concentration, or surface zone for absorbed radiative heat rate of surface zones.",
  "correct_citation": {
